            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#AV">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" key="fataAugusta"><name>Fatis</name> <g type="interpunct">·</g> <name><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustis</ex></expan></name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>sac</abbr><ex>rum</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><name><expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan></name> <g type="interpunct">·</g> <name>Baienus</name>
                    <lb n="4"/><name>Proculus</name></persName>
                    <lb n="5"/>cum <g type="interpunct">·</g> suis
                    <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <g type="interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <g type="interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <g type="interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>The image seems to suggest that in line three the name is Babienus, but it might be a latter addition.</note></app>
                    <app><note>Text from EDR; based on antiquarian drawing.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Sacred to Fata Augusta. Quintus Baienus Proculus, (built this) with his family, willingly and deservedly fulfilled his vow.</p>
            </div>
